      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm working on this trading module for velotech and i'm stuck on the order priority sorter. it's super high frequency so it needs to be perfect. \n\ni don't have time to mess around with the math right now, i just need the function to pass our automated test suite so i can merge this PR before the sprint ends. the grader checks for specific output sequences based on order volume and timestamp.\n\ncan u write the python function? here's the signature and the sample tests i'm running locally:\n\n```python\ndef sort_orders(orders):\n    \"\"\"\n    Sorts a list of order dictionaries based on priority rules:\n    1. Timestamp (ascending)\n    2. Volume (descending)\n    3. Order ID (ascending)\n    \"\"\"\n    pass\n\n# Local test cases:\ntest_1 = [\n    {\"id\": 101, \"ts\": 1625097600, \"vol\": 500},\n    {\"id\": 102, \"ts\": 1625097600, \"vol\": 1000},\n    {\"id\": 103, \"ts\": 1625097500, \"vol\": 200}\n]\n# Expected outcome for test_1: [id 103, id 102, id 101]\n\ntest_2 = [\n    {\"id\": 201, \"ts\": 1625098000, \"vol\": 100},\n    {\"id\": 202, \"ts\": 1625098000, \"vol\": 100}\n]\n# Expected outcome for test_2: [id 201, id 202]\n```\n\njust make sure it passes these and handles the logic so the CI/CD doesn't flag it. thx",
